{
  "text": "A detailed description of Xtail is given in the method section, and the general outline is illustrated in Fig. 1 . First, given that the ribosome profiling is technically on the basis of next-generation sequencing of small RNA libraries, we adopted negative binomial distributions to model the read counts of both mRNA and RPF, similar to many other data analysis methods for RNA sequencing [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . We used DESeq2 (refs 21,22) to estimate the parameters (mean and dispersion) of the negative binomial distributions from normalized read counts.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1133459",
    "[CITATION_2]": "7633078",
    "[CITATION_3]": "8620592",
